children.value: I decided to update all my Nuget's packages and one more time, WebGrease could not update correctly. The solution's projects compile but when executing them website on IIS an error message raises.
Could not load file or assembly 'WebGrease, Version=1.6.5135.21930, Culture=neutral, PublicKeyToken=31bf3856ad364e35' or one of its dependencies
The .dll in the project is also with the version 1.6.5135.21930.
So why does the project does not want to execute? The problem was that the
had a version that was taking over. You can go into the GAC's folders,
and see 3 folders. One for GAC_32, GAC_64 and GAC_MSIL. After deleting the
folder ones in those folders and then be sure that none of WebGrease is into the
Asp.Net Temporary** folders. To be also sure that the cache of Asp is not having the wrong DLL, be sure to clear C:
